<TITLE> Geeteara calls for civil-society efforts to help flood victims </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajbari, Aug 7 (bdnews.24.com) Industry adviser Geeteara Safiya Choudhury Tuesday called upon civil society to come forward to aid flood victims alongside the administration and the army. At a views-exchange meeting at the Rajbari Deputy Commissioner's Office Tuesday, she said, "We have to work together to combat the fury of the natural disaster." The adviser asked officials of the administration to keep a watch on women and children in the flood-affected areas. She also urged the businessmen not to increase the prices of commodities. Geeteara visited the flood-affected areas of Rajbari. She distributed relief materials among the distressed people at a flood shelter of Berabanga Masjid Council in town. She also distributed relief materials among people sheltering on the embankment in the Bharat union parishad, and enquired about their welfare. Deputy commissioner Towhida Bulbul presided over the meeting, also joined by army officers and local administration officials. bdnews24.c
